messages.content:
Heya @Leadership @Council 
We're making an in house Discord bot for the family. Please use this channel for discussions / requests
a feature that let us know who from our faction has revives on
Can it calculate rw payouts for us if we give it numbers? 🤣
Make a secret function for me that steals everyone's money and gives it to me
I think the main function we need is for it to automatically keep track of roles and stuff.  That used to be a pain in the butt when we had to do it manually.
We already have verification
Awesome
Technically yes, but that'd also be hell to do over Discord rather than Spreadsheets
Can you bring back something like the old Bot that gave family wide scores and competitions? Can't remember what yall called it was it tribes?
#BringBackTribes2024
How would yall feel about banking for each faction
Something to maybe make it a little easier and coordinated
The only problem is that only Leaders get bank access, so getting money sent relies on a small few being online.
I am not adamantly opposed to faction banking, personally, but relying on 3 of us to send funds if they are overseas? not gonna go well
Well just something that either pings yall and will give yall a link to do so I have a mock if you’re interested

Members would have to know that they wouldn't necessarily get immediate access to the funds if no leaders are online. Generally we tell people to just ask for loans in FC and repay when they get back to Torn.
Have something like this in a banker channel waiting that way a member can cancel if need be but yes they’d have to know it wouldn’t be immediate
so that could realistically ping `@(WHO|LW|GW|TW) Leadership` based on the requestor
Correct
I had an idea for this actually
It was rooted in allowing us to actually further restrict the money give permission to gold fist only but it also allows for getting money easier too
in TW we have a growing number of faction companies
these all hold a decent amount of cash in vault
a few hundred mil
which is enough to satisify most member requests
so the idea is that when a member requests for x money
it pings all of the directors (those willing to participate anyways)
and they can provide the member requesting money with the funds out of the company balance
but that amount is logged and then an add to bal link to generated for gold fist to adjust(increase) the balance of the player who provided the funds
Hmmm
That’s something that could be done id have to look at, would it be for all factions or just TW?
I like the idea in concept, but feel we would need Leaders+Council as faction company directors.
im not sure on the status of other facs
how many have council/leadership directors?
like in TW have kapt and chrono running faction companies
but steem and defiance (and soon me) are running personal comps but would probably be able to contribute to this as well
Maybe we could get some basic banking for each faction first and then go from there

does this detect for the request to be made outside of discord? ie if the player requests for x both through discord and in fac chat does the bot watch the faction log to see if the payment gets completed?
also, is the link a redirect link or just the torn link? if its a redirect link we can detect when its been clicked and block subsequent clicks
It’d be a manual completion but it could be setup to read faction log
Just a direct torn link
👌  i think we should hide it behind one of the buttons then
like a "pay" button and then it sends an ephemeral message to the user that clicked it with the payment link
and edits the initial message to something like "payment in progress" and polls the log for it to be completed
Yeah I mean that’s mostly how I have it setup currently
and if its not completed in like x seconds (60 maybe?) it goes back to the initial view for someone else to claim
and pings the first player who claimed it that they took too long and to no longer payout (or claim again to payout)
to prevent duplicate payouts
Yeah, that’s something that could be done
not inherently relevant to the bot but give this thread a R+ @everyone
https://www.torn.com/forums.php#/p=threads&f=63&t=16399202&b=0&a=0
hopefully if it gets implemented ill be able to make a script that allows for advanced tracking of RWs and correctly accounts for assists and sniping
I don't see that getting implemented unfortunately. No harm in asking though.
I was looking at double-entry accounting options for these types of things too.
We could probably look at adding something like that after a base implementation

If a bot on discord can be integrated that would be excellent. For leaders to input their transactions, etc.

I have stuff that downloads the entire funds history of the faction and I need to parse that, etc. So we can keep track of who is doing what.
But this is all in the works and I'm just theory crafting when I have the time.
Reason being is I'm sure it's been asked before because people wanted ways to track their ranked weapons going off on the specials and what not
Anyone have name / pfp suggestions for the bot
Currently lex offers no banking

Also if you went the route of having a bot track it maybe deliberately make it 5 mins behind or have it only visible to certain ranks otherwise thats open for abuse, not saying we have anyone untrustworthy but you never know what could happen if someone sees a request for say 150m and has a friend there not associated with publicly
Could have a request channel that sends it to a different channel
I see quite often the bot messages with a little icon saying only you can see this
Yeah it all depends on if they do (!)(command) or (/)(command)
But the idea would be each faction has their own channel to limit some issues and could make it so you can’t see the history
Currently it’s @Wolverine Watch

If you were gona go with Kings idea of having companies fulfill request why not have it so all leads can see it and then any faction could fulfill the request, at the end of the week or month it generates a message that says tw owes gw x amount or lw owes who etc so it balances every so often, across the family we must have 10+ people with banking perms and 1 active at almost any moment
That’s a good idea
And yeah the request channel should only be viewable by council and leadership
The request can be made from anywhere using slash commands
Instead of tracking balances in Torn bring it external to discord and have each fac with a float to fulfill
Hmmm
That could be open to issues with people requesting more than they’d have
True
Would you not log in a database what they have tho?
We can make an api call to check their balance in their home faction
But yeah it is a bit finicky
The way I do it as of now is do a call at the time they make the request
We wouldn’t have one source of truth
Unless we log all transactions which kinda becomes a pain
I guess the bot only needs to keep track of a difference tho
I think it may be better to just stick to a basic request system
So basically someone requests, all leads get a message, 1 lead fulfills and clicks a button then a new message is generated for the home fac to adjust balance and reimburse the sending party?
A players balance is their in game balance +/- the bot difference
It would mean requests MUST go through discord though
Rather than being optional
We would need to prohibit making banking requests through Roth
Torn*
Which will never happen and cause more issues

I mean, if the bot keeps a record of how much has been requested yet not repaid by faction, check that amount against user balance.... but then you'd need to reduce that amount on repayment by faction
Or take user balances as gospel truth and leads have to be hot on actioning balance changes
Maybe a persistent message in a chat until it sees the event that balance was adjusted by the correct amount
I mean as of right now when members request balance they ping and a lead gets to it when they can
I don’t necessarily see a reason to change that system up too terribly by adding in complications and failure points
right, any of this is only necessary if we want to promise fast money requests
which is only really necessary for xanax flyers 😛 (or rehab, i guess)

Our old faction had the motto of we’re not an ATM so we’ll get to you when we can which I feel like should be pretty true in any faction the only difference this would add would be ease on the banker to make the process a little quicker for them

Any money stored in a vac is dead money doing nothing for them

I tell them to get their money out of fac vault asap and into something living and breathing
We don't let them keep it in the vault 🤣
Rw funds get allocated then if not requested by the next rw there sent online or not

Its pretty simplistic in approach. Save the payout data in cache (I have local IndexedDB implementation). Have a button to set another variable to trigger modal on vault page and navigate. Vault page is a secondary match in the script headers. If the variable is set, open the modal, clear the variable so modal doesn't pop up every time. Only when coming from initial script page. Use the cached payout data to feed the modal. Pay button uses your same logic. Modal can be designed to replicate your other UI/UX design.
